   "action": "<ACOND () (RETURN <REMOVE-TRAVEL-COMMAND ,OUTSIDE-PRISON ,ENTER-COMMAND> <COND (,KIDNAPPED <TELL D ,KIDNAPPED \" was safe\">) (T <TELL \"We had saved the Dwarf\">)> <TELL \", but at what cost? I shuddered at our bad fortune and\ndreaded the trials that were yet to come.\" CR CR> <TELL \"Bergon approached, and laid his hand on my shoulder. \"We must\nput this behind us, \" TAG \". Agrith grieves for Hurth and also for\nhis besieged people; we must not let either down.\" And taking\nme by the arm, we left the field of battle.\" CR CR> <TELL \"As we passed the fork, Bergon noticed a device of some kind mounted on\nthe wall. \"Let's hope this opens the prison door,\" he said, and pressed it.\nMoving quickly, we lowered ourselves back down into the prison, where, indeed,\nthe door stood open. And as we left, the door closed silently behind us.\"> <MOVE-TO ,OUTSIDE-PRISON>)>",
