   "action": "<ACOND () (SCOUT:REMOVE <TELL ACT \" went off into both mines to check them out. \"The older mine is in\nbad shape,\" he reported, \"I fear it is nearly ready to collapse.\"\">) (BACK <TELL \"Having done all the exploring we could in the mines, we returned to the\nbottom of the stairs.\"> <REMOVE-TRAVEL-COMMAND ,MINE-LOWER-STAIR ,LEFT-COMMAND> <MOVE-TO ,MINE-LOWER-STAIR>) (NEW-MINE <TELL \"We made our way through the passage until we came to a small round\nchamber. At the far end, a cleft in the rock opened up a narrow\npassage\"> <COND (<NOT <QSET? ,MINER-PASSAGE ,SEEN>> <TELL \" through which a loud, tapping noise could be heard.\" CR CR> <TELL \"Praxix motioned toward the cleft. \"Shall we see who it is?\" he asked\">)> <MOVE-TO ,MINER-PASSAGE \".\">) (OLD-MINE <COND (<FSET? ,OLD-MINE ,SEEN> <REMOVE-TRAVEL-COMMAND ,HERE ,OLD-MINE-COMMAND> <TELL \"Again, I expressed my reservations about entering the old mine, but I\nwas assured by \"> <TELL D <FIRST-IN-PARTY ,BERGON ,PRAXIX>> <TELL \" that we would not enter the mine again after having\none last look. Reluctantly, I agreed. The wall boards groaned and creaked\nwith our every step, and it appeared that a loud sneeze could bring the whole\nmine down on top of us.\">) (T <TELL \"I was not very comfortable about the decision to enter this old mine. The\nancient wooden beams which were intended to hold up the walls and roof\nappeared barely able to help even themselves. As we moved, small pieces\nof rock fell from above, and a disturbing sound, like a sick groan, came\nfrom all around us.\">)> <MOVE-TO ,OLD-MINE>)>",
