   "action": "<ACOND () (SCOUT:REMOVE <TELL ACT \" tried to scout out the area, but the heavy mist made his task all\nbut impossible.\" CR CR> <COND (<EQUAL? ,ACTOR ,HURTH> <TELL \"\"I cannot say what lies ahead,\" he announced, \"though I have found\nsome heavy tracks in the mud which I fear to be orc footprints. We must be\ncareful, and move quietly!\"\">) (T <TELL \"\"It's not good,\" he said, \"There are footprints in the mud just ahead,\nand I doubt their owners are friendly.\"\">)>) (PROCEED <TELL \"Early the next morning, we started again. The air was heavy with mist,\nand it was difficult to see just a few paces before us. We had been moving\nsilently for an hour when \" D ,LEADER \" became alarmed.\" CR CR> <TELL \"Gathering together, we soon learned that Praxix was missing from our\nranks. \"Praxix! Praxix!\" we called, but there was no reply, only the\nsounds of the forest.\" CR CR> <TELL \"\"Praxix! Praxix!\" The words fell only upon the deaf ears of the forest.\"> <DIVIDER> <MAKE-SUBGROUP ,PRAXIX> <MOVE-TO ,TREE-FORK>)>",
