   "action": "<ACOND (\"AUX\" TMP) (DOWN <COND (<NOT <FSET? ,PRAXIX ,LIT>> <REMOVE-TRAVEL-COMMAND> <TELL \"It took only a few steps for Praxix to realize that the path leading inside\nthe mill mechanism was dark and potentially dangerous. Rather than risk injury,\nhe returned to the open air.\">) (T <COND (<NOT ,SUBGROUP-MODE> <TELL \"Praxix insisted in exploring the mechanism himself, and we soon wished that\nhe hadn't.\" CR CR> <MAKE-SUBGROUP ,PRAXIX>)> <TELL \"At first, it appeared that the passage was merely some maintenance path with\naccess to the internal working parts of the mill mechanism. However, the path\nsoon reached a set of stone steps that led down beneath ground level, ending\nat the junction of two paths.\" CR CR> <TELL \"But no sooner had Praxix started to think about where to proceed next, the\nground collapsed beneath the steps, and the resulting avalanche of stone\ncompletely buried his only known route to the outside.\"> <MOVE-TO ,XFER-JCN> <SET TMP <+ <PARTY-PCM ,PRAXIX> 1>> <SETG TAG-SWAP-CHR <GET ,PARTY .TMP>> <PUT ,PARTY <PARTY-PCM ,TAG> ,TAG-SWAP-CHR> <PUT ,PARTY .TMP ,TAG> <FSET ,TAG ,SHADOW> ;<SAVE-TAG-OBJECTS> <SCENE ,MILL-SCENE>)>) (PROCEED <LEAVE-MILL-AREA>)>",
