   "action": "<ACOND () (RETURN <REMOVE-TRAVEL-COMMAND ,BITE-FOREST ,BERGON-ROUTE-COMMAND> <MOVE-TO ,BITE-FOREST> <COND (<FSET? ,BERGON ,DEAD> <TELL \"Carrying Bergon's body on our shoulders,\">) (<FSET? ,BERGON ,TRAPPED> <TELL \"Unable to help Bergon, and with the snake-trees moving ever closer,\">) (T <TELL \"Carrying Bergon on our shoulders,\">)> <TELL \" we retreated to the safety of our camp.\"> <COND (<FSET? ,BERGON ,DEAD> <HINT ,HINT-TANGLETREES> <TELL CR CR \"We buried Bergon there, after a short ritual performed by Praxix.\">) (<NOT <FSET? ,BERGON ,TRAPPED>> <COND (<FSET? ,BITE-VICTIM ,INCAPACITATED> <TELL CR CR \"Bergon regained his strength quickly; he looked at \" D ,BITE-VICTIM \" and\nfrowned. \"We must do something quickly, or he will die!\"\">) (T <TELL CR CR \"It had been a long and frightening day; the sun had set, and we fell into\na deep and dreamless sleep.\"> <NEXT-DAY>)>) (T <FSET ,BERGON ,DEAD>)>) (<AND <ACTION? CAST> <OBJECT? LEVITATE-SPELL> <PRSI? BERGON-OBJECT>> <TELL \"Praxix tried using his spell of elevation, but the trees' grip was\ntoo strong.\">) (<AND <ACTION? CAST> <OBJECT? FIRE-SPELL>> <UNUSE-ESSENCES> <TELL \"Praxix started to reach for his fire and earth essence, but he stopped\nhimself. \"Not the best place for a bonfire,\" he said softly.\">) (<AND <ACTION? CAST> <OR <AND <OBJECT? LIGHTNING-SPELL> <PRSI? TANGLETREE>> <OBJECT? FAR-VISION-SPELL>>> <COND (<OBJECT? FAR-VISION-SPELL> <GRAPHIC ,G-TANGLEWOOD-BURNS>)> <COND (<IN? ,WESTFLAKE-ROOT ,PRAXIX> <TELL \"For the second time that day, \">)> <TELL \"Praxix put his magic to good use! \"> <COND (<OBJECT? LIGHTNING-SPELL> <FSET ,LIGHTNING-SPELL ,SEEN> <TELL \"He mixed together the essences of fire and water, then added just a pinch\nof earth essence. Just moments after casting the mixture, clouds gathered\naround him, and the sky turned black. He motioned with his\nstaff at the deadly tree and a bolt of white lightning struck it, splitting it\ndown the middle. A few branches caught fire, and instinctively withdrew,\nas if in pain.\"> <COND (<NOT <QSET? ,LIGHTNING-SPELL ,INCAPACITATED>> <TELL CR CR \"Praxix, proud of his accomplishment, turned to me and whispered that it\nwas the pinch of earth essence that really gives the lightning spell its\nadded punch. But however the magic had been prepared, its effect was\nprofound.\">)>) (T <TELL \"Praxix prepared his flare enchantment, and cast it at the tree before\nus. The ball of flame sped through the forest before us, and the tentacles\nwithdrew, as if in pain, clearing a path in its wake.\">)> <TELL \" The tentacles loosened, we retrieved Bergon from their deadly\nembrace.\"> <FCLEAR ,BERGON ,TRAPPED> <COND (<FSET? ,BERGON ,DEAD> <TELL \" But it was too late; Bergon was dead!\">) (T <PARTY-ADD ,BERGON> <MAKE-BUSY ,BERGON ,ILL-COMMAND> <TELL CR CR \"\"They don't much care for fire,\" Praxix mused, \"Let's get away before\nthey recover!\"\">)> <RTRUE>) (<AND <ACTION? EXAMINE> <OBJECT? BERGON-OBJECT>> <TELL ACT \" looked Bergon over; he was unconscious. The tentacles were\nslowly, inexorably, squeezing the life out of him!\">)>",
