   "action": "<ACOND () (PROCEED <TELL \"Ahead, the passage opened up into a wider hall, and we moved quickly\nin anticipation of escape. But the hall ended blindly. All around,\nthe sound of water was nearly deafening, and moment by moment, the\ndull thump of orc footsteps moved ever closer; it appeared that tragedy\nwas close at hand.\"> <MOVE-TO ,ABOVE-FLUME>) (<OR <ACTION? BACK> <AND <ACTION? SCOUT> <NOT <QSET? ,HERE ,SCOUTED>>>> <UPDATE-FSET ,HERE ,DONT-SCOUT> <REMOVE-PARTY-COMMAND ,BACK-COMMAND> <COND (<ACTION? BACK> <SETG ACTOR <FIRST-IN-PARTY ,HURTH ,ESHER ,PRAXIX>>)> <TELL \"Rather than attempt to retrace our steps and fall into the hands of\nthe orcs, we sent \" ACT \" to quickly and quietly check out our rear.\nMoments later, he returned. \"They are not far behind, but they\nmove more slowly and there is hope in that.\"\" CR CR> <TELL \"\"I fear there is another explanation,\" Praxix replied gloomily, and we\nsoon found out what he meant.\">)>",
