   "action": "<ACOND () (GET-ADVICE:REMOVE <TELL \"Bergon reminded us that Astrix had said the Dwarvish gate was west\nof our position\"> <COND (<FSET? ,HERE ,SCOUTED> <TELL \", and suggested taking the northern route, it being\nthe closest to due west. He solicited advice from the others in the\ngroup, who were all in general agreement.\">) (T <TELL \". The problem, we reminded him, was that both paths appeared to be\nheading in a westerly direction, giving no obvious sign as to which would\nbe the best route to take.\">)>) (SCOUT:REMOVE <FSET ,HERE ,SCOUTED> <TELL ACT \" sped off into the forest, returned, then sped off down the other fork.\nWhen he returned, he offered no help in our decision.\" CR CR> <TELL \"\"Both paths appear to run roughly west, though I'd say the northern\npath is a bit more direct,\" he said.\">) (NORTH-ROUTE <SETG A-B-FLAG T> <TELL \"We chose the more northerly path, and by day's end we had reached the\nplace described by Astrix as the Dwarvish gate of Bern i-Fen.\"> <TELL ,FOREST-NIGHT> <TELL CR CR \"When we awoke the next morning, a cold wind blew from the north, yet\na dark shroud of mist lay over the forest. It seemed an ill-omened day,\nand our hearts were heavy with uncertainty and doubt. I packed our\nthings, and our party approached the gate.\"> <MOVE-TO ,FOREST-GATE>) (SOUTH-ROUTE <TELL \"Choosing the more southerly path, we moved quickly as the forest appeared\nto become older and darker. Rather than entering this foreboding forest so\nlate in the day, we camped just outside.\"> <TELL ,FOREST-NIGHT> <TELL \" We rose to a cold, but sunny morning and were soon\nin the midst of the dark forest.\"> <SCENE ,TANGLESCENE> <MOVE-TO ,TANGLEWOOD-1>)>",
