   "action": "<ACOND () (<FSET? ,HERE ,ENCHANTED> <FCLEAR ,HERE ,ENCHANTED> <COND (<AND <ACTION? CAST> <OBJECT? WIND-SPELL>> ;\"Double whammy...\" <USE-ESSENCES ,WIND-SPELL> <COND (<G? <GET-TEMP> 13> <TELL \"Using more air essence than he would have liked, Praxix cast a wind spell at\nthe levitated raft, blowing it (and us) across to the far shore of the river,\nwhere we tumbled onto the ground.\"> <CROSSED-RIVER>) (T <TELL \"It was far too risky to try blowing us across the entire expanse of river, but\nthere was enough air essence in Praxix' pouch to propel us back to the near shore,\nwhere we landed in a twisted heap, destroying the raft entirely.\"> <FCLEAR ,RAFT ,SEEN> <MOVE-TO ,RIVER-2>)>) (T <TELL \"It wasn't long before we found out. We watched, helplessly as our raft sank\ndown into the churning waters and started drifting downstream. \"> <SETG ACTION ,UPSTREAM-COMMAND> <RIVER-MOVE 1>)>) (CROSS <RIVER-MOVE 6>) (DOWNSTREAM <RIVER-MOVE 1>) (UPSTREAM <RIVER-MOVE 1>) (RETURN <RIVER-MOVE -4>) (<AND <ACTION? CAST> <OBJECT? RAIN-SPELL>> <SAVE-SPELL> <REMOVE ,HYE-RIVER> <TELL \"It wasn't particularly funny when Praxix cast his rain spell and the\nlevel of the river grew even higher.\" CR CR> <COND (<IN-PARTY? ,ESHER> <TELL \"\"Will somebody take that child's toys away from him?\" Esher snarled.\">) (T <TELL \"\"I think we've had enough magic for the present,\" Bergon said, trying\nhis best to conceal his anger.\">)>) (<AND <ACTION? CAST> <OBJECT? LEVITATE-SPELL> <FSET? ,HERE ,TRAPPED> <NOT <QSET? ,HERE ,ENCHANTED>>> <TELL \"Praxix hurriedly attempted to cast an elevation spell to forestall\nour encounter with the falls, and this he accomplished not a moment before\nwe were to plunge over the falls.\"> <COND (<IN-PARTY? ,BERGON> <TELL CR CR \"\"Out of curiosity,\" Bergon asked, turning to Praxix, \"what happens when\nthe enchantment wears off?\"\">)>) (<AND <ACTION? CAST> <OBJECT? LEVITATE-SPELL>> <SAVE-SPELL> <UNUSE-ESSENCES> <TELL \"Praxix thought to cast his elevation spell on the raft, but the situation\nwas not yet serious enough to take such a risk.\">)>",
