   "action": "<ACOND () (GET-ADVICE:REMOVE <TELL ACT \" asked for advice, and between us we thought up a few suggestions, all bad.\nWe would certainly be massacred if we attempted storming the orc camp, and even\nthen we could not know where \" D ,TRAP-VICTIM \" was being held.\"> <COND (<AND <FSET? ,ACTIVE-MINE ,SOLVED> <NOT <FSET? ,RED-ROCK ,DEAD>>> <TELL CR CR \"\"I wish I knew how the miner did it,\" I said, wistfully thinking back to\nhis magical disappearances.\">)> <RTRUE>) (<AND <ACTION? INVENTORY> <NOT <QSET? ,HERE ,EXAMINED>>> <TELL \"The situation appeared grim, and I wondered if there might be anything\nin my pack which would help.\"> <COND (<IN? ,RED-ROCK ,INVENTORY> <FSET ,RED-ROCK ,DEAD> <TELL \" To my astonishment, I came up literally empty-handed, for as I pulled my\nhand from the pack, I found it to be entirely transparent. And then I\nput two pieces together: the disappearing miner and the pieces of red rock\nthat had inadvertantly fallen from his sack.\" CR CR> <TELL \"Reaching back into the pack, I noticed that some powder had been scraped\noff one of the red rocks. \"A magical reagent!\" I said to myself, proud to have\nmade such an important discovery. \"Praxix will be pleased - if we find him,\nthat is.\"\"> <TRAVEL-COMMANDS ,TAG ,PICK-UP-COMMAND ,USE-COMMAND ,INVENTORY-COMMAND>) (T <TELL \" It appeared there was not; \"> <COND (<FSET? ,ACTIVE-MINE ,SOLVED> <TELL \"how I wished we had found the secret to the miner's disappearing trick.\nIt would certainly come in handy just about now!\">) (T <TELL \"I sighed deeply, certain that \" D ,TRAP-VICTIM \" was beyond help.\">)>)>) (USE <SETG RED-ROCK-COUNT <- ,RED-ROCK-COUNT 1>> <RESTORE-TAG-COMMANDS> <TELL \"Determined to save \" D ,TRAP-VICTIM \", I took one of the red rocks\nfrom my pack and pummelled it into a fine powder which I then spread across\nmy body. In a matter of moments, I was completely invisible! Not\nknowing how long the powder would work, I moved quickly into the heart of\nthe orcs' camp.\" CR CR> <TELL \"It took quite a while, but I finally found \" D ,TRAP-VICTIM \", bound and\ngagged inside a tent alongside the cooking area.\" CR CR> <TELL \"\"Psst! \" D ,TRAP-VICTIM \"!\" I whispered from just beside his right ear.\nHe nearly jumped out of his bonds at the sound of my voice.\" CR CR> <TELL \"\"Mmgmm rumggm,\" he said frantically through his gag.\" CR CR> <TELL \"\"Calm down,\" I said, \"I'm just invisible.\" It didn't take long to\nfree him, but we now faced a difficult decision.\"> <PARTY-ADD ,TRAP-VICTIM> <MAKE-SUBGROUP ,TAG ,TRAP-VICTIM> <MOVE-TO ,ORCS-CAMP>) (SCOUT:REMOVE <TELL ACT \" went off to scout out the orcs camp. A few minutes later, he\nreturned.\" CR CR> <TELL \"\"Lots of orcs,\" he said, panting, \"but no sign of \" D ,TRAP-VICTIM \". He's probably being held in one of the tents.\"\">) (TO-CAMP:REMOVE <TELL \"One thought was to enter the orcs' camp, and attempt to find our\ncaptured friend. But the odds of success were staggeringly small;\nafter all, \" <I-WAS/WE-WERE 2> \" not invisible! No, that would not work, but \" <I/WE 2> \" felt that there must be some strategy that would.\">) (TO-PRAXIX <LEAVE-VICTIM-WITH-ORCS>)>",
   "descfcn": null,
