   "action": "<ACOND () (ACCEPT <TELL ,VERY-KIND CR CR> <CHOOSE-ZEPHYR> <RETURN-FROM-WHARF> <END-OPTION>) (CONSIDER <TELL-CONSIDER> <MOVE-TO ,WHARF> <END-OPTION>) (LIE <TELL \"\"We're heading south, to the Isle of Estril,\" Bergon said. It\nwas a lie, of course, but it was roughly in the right direction.\" CR CR> <TELL \"\"Estril? What on earth would send you there?\" the captain scowled. \"No,\ndon't tell me. If that's where you're headed, I can take you.\"\"> <OPTION ,BERGON ,ACCEPT-COMMAND ,CONSIDER-COMMAND>) (TELL-TRUTH <FSET ,HERE ,TRUTHFUL> <TELL \"\"We were hoping to sail to the Misty Isle.\"\" CR CR> <TELL \"The old man's eyes widened. \"The Misty Isle,\" he repeated. Then, he sat\nfor a long while before speaking again.\" CR CR> <TELL \"\"Lots of legends about the Misty Isle,\" he said, snivelling, \"and ain't\nnone of them wouldn't keep you up nights. They say that none's returned\nthat's gone there. No, I'm afraid I'm not young enough or drunk enough to\ntry it. Tell you what - I can take you as far as Estril. Could be there's\nboats you can hire there that'll take you where you're heading.\"\"> <OPTION ,BERGON ,ACCEPT-COMMAND ,CONSIDER-COMMAND>)>",
