   "loc": null,
   "flags": [],
   "synonyms": [],
   "adjectives": [],
   "action": "<EXECUTE () <COND (<NOT <QSET? ,HINT-JAIL ,SEEN>> <TELL \"We were trapped in the jail with no escape possible. There is no one to\nblame, nothing we could have done.\"> <RTRUE>) (<FSET? ,GRAY-STONE ,SOLVED> <TELL \"I wonder about the gray reagent we had bought. Could some mixture\nhave helped us? If so, we would have done better to experiment before\ngetting caught!\">) (<NOT <FSET? ,CURIO-SHOP ,SCOUTED>> <TELL \"And yet, we did not explore everywhere in town. Not the curio shop,\nat any rate.\">) (<FSET? ,GRAY-STONE ,TRAPPED> <TELL \"But why was Praxix so ornery; why didn't he ask to see some of the things\nthat were for sale in the curio shop? There might have been something\nuseful there.\">) (<NOT <FSET? ,GRAY-STONE ,EXAMINED>> <TELL \"Alas that we did not try to buy the gray stone. Later, Praxix confided\nthat it was a magical reagent, and its magic could have helped us.\">) (<NOT <QSET? ,HINT-JAIL ,SOLVED>> <TELL \"Alas that we had nothing to trade for the gray stone. It was certainly\na magical reagent, and might have helped us escape from jail.\"> <RTRUE>) (<NOT <FSET? ,STAIR-CHASM ,SEEN>> <TELL \"I think back to all we had accomplished, everything we had seen: was there\nany place we did not explore? Yes! The left stair in the caverns; but now\nI will never know what lay along that path.\">) (<NOT <FSET? ,FAR-CHASM ,SEEN>> <TELL \"The chasm between the broken stairs! I don't know why, but it occurs to me\nthat we never found a way across. Could that have helped?\">) (<NOT <FSET? ,SUNSET-TOWER ,SOLVED>> <TELL \"The Sunset Tower: why do I feel that we have missed simething there? Was\nthere something hidden there?\">) (T <TELL \"The spyglass! Of course! Praxix said it was a priceless treasure!\">)> <UPDATE-REMOVE ,HINT-JAIL>>",
