  "PATH-TO-MILL": {
   "name": "PATH-TO-MILL",
   "kind": "constant",
   "file": "fog.zil",
   "line": 172,
   "value": "\"The path snaked and wound its way toward the west, ending at the\nside of a river, which Praxix assumed to be the very same that\nwe had followed from the underground caverns. The remains of an\nold building stood here, crumbling; inside, a badly rusted\nmechanism sat. Praxix imagined it would be used for the grinding\nof grain.\""
  },
  "MOAT-DESC": {
   "name": "MOAT-DESC",
   "kind": "constant",
   "file": "fog.zil",
   "line": 180,
   "value": "\"Soon the forest\ngave way to a clearing, in the middle of which stood the ruins of a moated\ncastle. What little remained of the bridge hung tentatively over the\nwater, making any crossing a speculative affair.\""
  },
