  "ARMED-CREATURES": {
   "name": "ARMED-CREATURES",
   "kind": "constant",
   "file": "lake.zil",
   "line": 992,
   "value": "\", a group of armed creatures turned the corner and, catching sight of\nme, let out a horrific scream and raced in my direction. Having no other choice,\nI sprinted back to the pool and dove in, eventually making my way back to\""
  },
  "UL-DROPPED": {
   "name": "UL-DROPPED",
   "kind": "global",
   "file": "lake.zil",
   "line": 1108,
   "value": "0"
  },
  "NARROW-POOL": {
   "name": "NARROW-POOL",
   "kind": "constant",
   "file": "lake.zil",
   "line": 1182,
   "value": "\"I dove into the pool, and carefully started to descend. This was no ordinary pool,\nhowever; it was a tube, and a narrow one at that. After a short while, the tube\ncurved and narrowed, so much so that it was soon difficult to proceed. Discouraged,\nI returned to the surface.\""
  },
  "CHEAT": {
   "name": "CHEAT",
   "kind": "global",
   "file": "lavos.zil",
   "line": 7,
   "value": "<>"
  },
  "LEAVE-LAVOS": {
   "name": "LEAVE-LAVOS",
   "kind": "constant",
   "file": "lavos.zil",
   "line": 241,
   "value": "\"It was mid-afternoon when we left Lavos, heading south. The road,\nwhich soon narrowed to a simple foot path, wound its way down into a deep\ncanyon, surrounded by sheer walls. After a short time, we found ourselves\nat a fork in the path, the left branch leading east along the foothills and\nthe right one continuing down the valley to the south. Both appeared desolate\nand poorly traveled. I wondered which path Garlimon's party had taken, and\nhow near they had come to reaching Astrix. And then, a cold, bone-dry wind\narose from the north, filling me with dread.\""
  },
  "MINAR-INTRO": {
   "name": "MINAR-INTRO",
   "kind": "constant",
   "file": "lavos.zil",
   "line": 480,
   "value": "\"\"I am called Minar, and I have travelled often in the Outlands. You are in\ngreat danger, whether you know it or not. If you will have me, I offer you my\nservices.\" Minar's eyes flickered with a disturbing light, but saying nothing,\nwe awaited the decision of Bergon.\""
  },
